    "title": "Siloed-borrowing risk controls are dead code and can be bypassed entirely",
    "locations": [
      "0xaef900f14710d067ae96555486232c7189784f50/contracts/protocol/libraries/logic/ValidationLogic.sol:253",
      "0xaef900f14710d067ae96555486232c7189784f50/contracts/protocol/libraries/configuration/UserConfiguration.sol:196",
      "0xaef900f14710d067ae96555486232c7189784f50/contracts/protocol/libraries/configuration/ReserveConfiguration.sol:303"
    ],
    "claim": "The protocol defines siloed-borrowing state (`getSiloedBorrowingState`, `getSiloedBorrowing`, and `SILOED_BORROWING_VIOLATION`) but `ValidationLogic.validateBorrow()` never checks any of them. As a result, a borrower can open additional borrows even when one reserve is configured as siloed, defeating the isolation assumptions that reserve parameters rely on.",
    "impact": "If any listed reserve is intended to be siloed, users can combine it with other borrows anyway. That breaks the protocol's core risk model for volatile/illiquid assets and can turn what should be isolated exposure into cross-reserve bad debt.",
    "paths": [
      "borrow() -> BorrowLogic.executeBorrow() -> ValidationLogic.validateBorrow()"
    ]
  },
