    "claim": "`executeLiquidateERC721()` prices the seized NFT against `params.liquidationAsset`, validates only that the borrower has some global debt (`globalDebt != 0`), and then calls `_supplyNewCollateral()` to deposit that asset for the borrower. It never requires that the borrower actually owes the chosen `liquidationAsset`, and it never burns any debt in that reserve.",
    "impact": "Every listed reserve asset becomes a liquidation vector for every NFT-backed position. If a listed asset has a weaker oracle or can be temporarily overpriced, an attacker can seize valuable NFT collateral by paying in that asset at an inflated oracle value while the borrower's original debt remains outstanding, worsening solvency.",
