    "claim": "Before `executeSupplyERC721FromNToken()` remints the NToken, `validateSupplyFromNToken()` requires `IERC721(reserveCache.xTokenAddress).ownerOf(tokenId) == address(0)`. On standard ERC721 implementations, `ownerOf()` reverts for nonexistent tokens instead of returning the zero address, so the validation itself reverts whenever the NToken id has not already been minted.",
    "impact": "Any path that relies on re-supplying an NFT already held by the NToken without an extra underlying transfer is effectively unusable. That creates a protocol-level denial of service for recovery, migration, or atomic re-collateralization flows built on `supplyERC721FromNToken`.",
